message: Does anyone heard about Intel-i7 Xtreme edition, with 8-cores!
story: Ahmed Adel shared a link to the group: Egyptian Geeks.
name: Intel® Core™ i7 Processor Extreme Edition
caption: intel.com
description: Unlocked and overclocked to maximize performance for the most intensive gaming and multimedia jobs.

data.message: Not exactly related by might be interesting for hardware enthusiasts, I found out that the latest AMD processors run at very high speeds, for example the FX-9590 runs at 4.7 GHz (and overclocks to 5.0 GHz turbo mode), has 8 cores and needs 220 W of power to operate ... such a beast, I can't imagine what kind of cooling it needs.
Mmm. AMD processors are good, but my beast here have 20M cache editions, and 3.7 GHz without any overclocking.

I didn't mean it's good, but just very power and cooling hungry :)
this "beast" is beaten by the non-extreme i7 4770K in many tests :D كارثة
for comparison, the i7 4770K runs at 3.5 GHz, has 4 cores and needs 84 W of power.
Source: http://www.anandtech.com/show/8316/amds-5-ghz-turbo-cpu-in-retail-the-fx9590-and-asrock-990fx-extreme9-review/6
